hopobject.body: I'm a trainee finddoctor.co.za The two-year renovation project was never going to be easy, even for someone with creative nous, the contacts and experience of Guild, who set up her interiors business in 1970 with a little shop on the King’s Road, south-west London. By the time she and her husband, the restaurateur Richard Polo, spotted Le Contesse, her business, Designers Guild, was already turning over several million pounds a year.
